                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "Most likely, what you are seeing is memory being held onto by the memory pool for future re-use. Arrow uses Jemalloc by default on Linux. You can check this by running\u00a0{{os.environ['ARROW_DEFAULT_MEMORY_POOL'] = 'system'}} prior to your code snippet, which should result in more consistent memory usage.\r\n\r\nCould you try that? And if you still think you see a memory leak, could you share the output you are seeing from the above snippet?",
